article.headline: Dayton 31, Robert Morris 14
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio -- Matt Smyth returned an interception 38 yards for a touchdown to lead a Dayton defense that had four picks, as the Flyers cruised 31-14 over Robert Morris Saturday for their tenth straight win. Dayton's Steve Valentino had five catches for 55 yards, and Joe Gulick had seven rushes for 58 yards to lead an offensive attack that was overshadowed by defensive play. The Flyers (3-0) had 300 yards in total offense to Robert Morris' 368. Robert Morris' James O'Quinn caught an 81-yard touchdown pass from Erik Cwalinski in the second quarter to enable the Colonials (1-2) to close the gap to 10-7. But Dayton scored late in the quarter on a 1-yard touchdown run by Ben Shappie to give the Flyers breathing room they wouldn't relinquish. O'Quinn had six catches for 137 yards. Cwalinski threw for 223 yards but his four interceptions gave Dayton the edge.
